          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>St Louis</placeName>
                                        <date>Nov 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 53</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Respected Sir</p>
                              <p>I avail myself of this first opportunity to put<lb/> myself in
                                                  <add>?</add>irtolary communication with you<lb/>
                                        to me always a pleasurable task.</p>
                              <p>How<add>?</add> be assur'd sir your great and truly<lb/> valuable
                                        labors are estimated at there right<lb/> value both by
                                        myself and all our brethren<lb/> here <sic>resillent</sic>
                                        in <placeName>St Louis</placeName> and quite<lb/> appropo to
                                        the above is our desire to<lb/> see and peruse your present
                                        task—<lb/>the translation of the Bible which we<lb/> trust
                                        you will soon pleasure us with<lb/> as in our occasional
                                        spiritual combats<lb/> we suffer from the difficulty that
                                        the Line<lb/> in the fable complained of our opponents<lb/>
                                        being the painters.</p>
                              <p>In regard to (what I flatter myself will<lb/> greatly interest you)
                                        our progress onward<lb/> I am happy to be able to inform
                                        you<lb/> that it is all you or any other believer<lb/> in
                                        the Immutable decrees and<lb/> Laws of our great Father
                                        could desire<lb/> At our last annual meeting we
                                        re-el-<lb/>ected our present worthy president<lb/>
                                        <persName>A J Lats Esqr.</persName>
                                        <persName>Joseph Kohn</persName> was</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>also re elected Treasurer <persName>Messrs. Samuel<lb/>
                                                  Newmark</persName>, and, <persName>Abhs</persName>
                                        Trustees and<lb/>
                                        <persName>H Myers</persName> Secetay<add>?</add> this also
                                        empowerd<lb/> their officers to negotiate for the
                                        purchase<lb/> of a suitable building for a
                                                  <sic>synagouge</sic><lb/> failing in this to
                                        purchase a lot and<lb/> erect one the Building we at
                                        present<lb/> occupy being ineligible on account of<lb/> time
                                        and situation.</p>
                              <p>Enclosed Dear Sir please find<lb/> five dollars for which you
                                        will<lb/> give me credit you will however<lb/> oblige me by
                                        forwarding <persName>English's</persName><lb/> grounds of
                                                  <sic>christianity</sic> Examined as I<lb/> am
                                        desirous of having it from your<lb/> recommendation other
                                        Books that<lb/> I wrote to you about I find I can<lb/> get
                                        them of <persName>Mr Lots</persName> which will<lb/> answer
                                        the same purpose. We have<lb/> not yet received the Occident for<lb/>
                                        <date>October</date>. You must excuse this<lb/> scrawling as
                                        I write by night<lb/> and my Light is none of the best<lb/>
                                        praying for your welfare</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">I Remain Yours Very</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">Respect <persName role="author">Henry
                                                  Myers</persName></p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">
                                        <placeName>Box 1515</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>I avail myself of this<lb/> to send my respects to you<lb/> and
                                        also Three Dollars<lb/> I necessitated from <persName>Mr
                                                  Waldstein</persName><lb/> for Occident.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Yours</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)"><persName>A J Laz</persName>—</p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Editor Occident</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <placeName>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">Pa</hi>
                                        </placeName>
                              </p>
